content.description: Climb first 5 bolts, shared with On Safari and El Nino.  At 5th bolt, head right through a gear section, to a few more bolts.  Good warm-up for the Visions Wall.  A little dirty, will be an excellent route when it cleans up.
content.protection: 8 bolts, gear to 2".  Fixed anchors off to the left.

content.description: Start off of a ledge system uphill from the Paisano Buttress. Lean over to clip the first bolt and pull onto the wall. After a few strenuous moves the climbing eases off. Place a few pieces and head for a two bolt anchor near the base of a tree above.

Cruxy low section with shallow pockets and small crimps.  Fire for a jug rail past the third bolt, and continue up on easier climbing through chickenheads and knobs.  For a little extra, hang a left at the 7th bolt and finish on La Nina.
content.location: Farthest right route on the Safari Wall.

content.description: Climb the first 3 bolts of La Nina, but instead of going up and left, continue traversing right on the flake.  Clip a bolt with a black hanger, and head slightly right and up to join the last 4 bolts of El Jefe.  Helps to have a long runner on the last bolt of La Nina and the first bolt of El Jefe.  Not the best route, but a fully-bolted moderate if you don't have any gear.
